    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DOOR CONTROL SWITCH</title>
        <para>The rotary door control switch is located in the driver's area. The function of the switch is to activate
            the solenoid on the air valve and turn the step light on and off. Refer to the Electrical for wiring
            schematic details. Periodic maintenance is required to torque mounting nut and wire attachment screws.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700153">Figure 48</hotlnk>
            for more information on doors and accessories.
        </para>
